# UI Components & CSS

- **All styles live in a CSS file.** Every component has a co-located `.css` or `.module.css` file. No inline CSS for anything.
- **No `style={{ }}`.** Do not use the `style` prop or inline style objects.
- **No style strings.** Do not use inline `style="..."` in JSX/HTML.

```tsx
# ✅ GOOD
// Button.tsx
import './Button.css'
export function Button({ children }) {
  return <button className="btn">{children}</button>
}

# ❌ BAD
<button style={{ padding: 8, color: 'blue' }}>Click</button>
<div style={{ marginTop: 16 }}>...</div>
<span style="font-weight: bold">...</span>
```

Use classes (and CSS modules if you prefer) in the co-located CSS file for all layout, spacing, colors, and typography.
